Not only that, but dairy,
in particular milk,

00:13:07.270 --> 00:13:10.630
has been shown to
increase estrogen in males

00:13:10.630 --> 00:13:14.290
by 26% within an
hour of consumption.

00:13:14.290 --> 00:13:15.929
Now as a bodybuilder,
the last thing

00:13:15.929 --> 00:13:17.470
you want floating
around in your body

00:13:17.470 --> 00:13:20.980
is more estrogen because you
can't produce muscle as good.

00:13:20.980 --> 00:13:22.480
So you want your
testosterone levels

00:13:22.480 --> 00:13:24.880
to be as high as possible and
manage your estrogen levels

00:13:24.880 --> 00:13:26.920
as closely as possible.

00:13:26.920 --> 00:13:28.780
Not only that,
but what was shown

00:13:28.780 --> 00:13:31.480
was that increased
estrogen levels also

00:13:31.480 --> 00:13:33.800
put you more at risk to
certain types of cancers,

00:13:33.800 --> 00:13:38.334
particularly prostate cancer
and breast cancer in females.

00:13:38.334 --> 00:13:40.000
And this number was
quite alarming to me

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:45.150
because 8 out of 10 men
who reached the age of 80

00:13:45.150 --> 00:13:47.829
develop some type of
prostate cancer cells.

00:13:47.829 --> 00:13:49.620
Doesn't mean they're
diagnosed with cancer,

00:13:49.620 --> 00:13:53.970
but they are at a much higher
risk of developing cancer

00:13:53.970 --> 00:13:56.050
at the old age.

00:13:56.050 --> 00:14:00.140
Now I mentioned earlier
about inflammation

00:14:00.140 --> 00:14:02.350
and how dairy can
cause inflammation.

00:14:02.350 --> 00:14:04.570
Well, it turns out
there is a sugar

00:14:04.570 --> 00:14:08.050
molecule that's called Neu5Gc.

00:14:08.050 --> 00:14:10.690
And, basically, this
molecule is exclusively

00:14:10.690 --> 00:14:14.710
found in dairy and
in meat products.

00:14:14.710 --> 00:14:17.310
So by consuming this
molecule, what happens

00:14:17.310 --> 00:14:20.860
is that your body
recognizes this as a threat.

00:14:20.860 --> 00:14:23.490
So your body will start
to produce antibodies,

00:14:23.490 --> 00:14:25.530
and these antibodies
will cause your body

00:14:25.530 --> 00:14:28.500
to become in a chronic
state of inflammation.

00:14:28.500 --> 00:14:31.200
And what happens when your
body is chronically inflamed

00:14:31.200 --> 00:14:35.130
is that the amount of blood
flow that your body is producing

00:14:35.130 --> 00:14:37.000
becomes greatly restricted.

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:41.580
And, of course, if you are
trying to get pumped in the gym

00:14:41.580 --> 00:14:45.060
and produce as much blood flow
in your veins to shuttle all

00:14:45.060 --> 00:14:47.430
the nutrients and oxygen to
your muscles to provide you

00:14:47.430 --> 00:14:49.240
power to push you
through those workouts,

00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:51.650
this is the last thing
that you would want.

00:14:51.650 --> 00:14:52.890
So I was very intrigued.

00:14:52.890 --> 00:14:55.230
And by this point, I was
already completely convinced

00:14:55.230 --> 00:14:57.270
that I had made
the right decision.

00:14:57.270 --> 00:14:59.880
And what I found was
that what would happen

00:14:59.880 --> 00:15:02.460
if I replaced those dairy
calories that I was normally

00:15:02.460 --> 00:15:04.500
getting with more
plants, and the results

00:15:04.500 --> 00:15:06.390
were quite astounding.

00:15:06.390 --> 00:15:09.120
Basically, what happens
is plant-based diets

00:15:09.120 --> 00:15:12.240
have been shown to decrease
the risk of prostate cancer

00:15:12.240 --> 00:15:14.130
by up to 35%.

00:15:14.130 --> 00:15:17.530
Now I don't know about you guys,
but whenever I'm 80 years old,

00:15:17.530 --> 00:15:18.610
I want to be healthy.

00:15:18.610 --> 00:15:20.179
I want to be happy,
and I definitely

00:15:20.179 --> 00:15:22.720
don't want to be dealing with
something like prostate cancer.

00:15:22.720 --> 00:15:24.610
So this was a huge
benefit for me.

00:15:24.610 --> 00:15:27.450
Not only that, but plants almost
exclusively contain something

00:15:27.450 --> 00:15:29.100
called antioxidants.

00:15:29.100 --> 00:15:32.640
Now antioxidants decrease
the body's inflammatory state

00:15:32.640 --> 00:15:35.640
by basically binding
themselves to free radicals

00:15:35.640 --> 00:15:37.980
that are produced through
oxidative processes

00:15:37.980 --> 00:15:38.640
in your system.

00:15:38.640 --> 00:15:41.820
So they bind themselves and
basically detoxify your system,

00:15:41.820 --> 00:15:43.920
thus, increasing the
amount of blood flow

00:15:43.920 --> 00:15:47.290
that you can have
during exercises.

00:15:47.290 --> 00:15:51.370
Also, plants are rich in fiber,
which decrease blood pressure

00:15:51.370 --> 00:15:53.320
and increase
insulin sensitivity.

00:15:53.320 --> 00:15:57.380
And insulin is another
hormone that is essentially--

00:15:57.380 --> 00:16:00.580
its purpose is to shuttle
nutrients into the cells.

00:16:00.580 --> 00:16:03.250
So when it comes to
recovery, you definitely

00:16:03.250 --> 00:16:05.590
want this hormone
to be fully active

00:16:05.590 --> 00:16:07.600
and shuttling as much
nutrients for recovery

00:16:07.600 --> 00:16:10.790
and rebuilding as possible.

00:16:10.790 --> 00:16:13.330
Also, plants contain
something called nitrates.

00:16:13.330 --> 00:16:16.540
Nitrates basically act
as vessel dilators,

00:16:16.540 --> 00:16:19.900
which dilate your blood vessels
to allow for more blood flow

00:16:19.900 --> 00:16:21.790
to reach your muscles.

00:16:21.790 --> 00:16:24.910
And they increase the
amount of oxygen utilization

00:16:24.910 --> 00:16:25.840
during exercise.

00:16:25.840 --> 00:16:28.060
So one study even
showed that simply

00:16:28.060 --> 00:16:31.630
by drinking beetroot
juice before exercise,

00:16:31.630 --> 00:16:35.649
maybe an hour or two before,
can increase your performance

00:16:35.649 --> 00:16:36.190
by up to 20%.

00:16:39.430 --> 00:16:42.940
So after I made this decision
to completely give up

00:16:42.940 --> 00:16:46.540
dairy products, I had
also made a commitment

00:16:46.540 --> 00:16:50.960
to compete in my very
first bodybuilding show.

00:16:50.960 --> 00:16:53.680
I made it very difficult for
myself because, first of all,

00:16:53.680 --> 00:16:56.200
this was the first ever show
that I had ever competed in,

00:16:56.200 --> 00:16:57.940
and I was a brand new vegan.

00:16:57.940 --> 00:16:59.470
And I had no idea
how to structure

00:16:59.470 --> 00:17:00.840
a diet for a bodybuilding show.

00:17:00.840 --> 00:17:04.300
So I had to adapt what I was
reading, what I was learning,

00:17:04.300 --> 00:17:06.910
and make it work for my body.

00:17:06.910 --> 00:17:08.710
And what happened was
really quite amazing

00:17:08.710 --> 00:17:11.200
is I only had about
eight weeks to prepare.

00:17:11.200 --> 00:17:14.050
And, lo and behold,
I step on stage,

00:17:14.050 --> 00:17:16.450
and I win the entire contest.

00:17:16.450 --> 00:17:19.180
I sweep every single
division, and I took home

00:17:19.180 --> 00:17:24.400
a stupid amount of hardware.

00:17:24.400 --> 00:17:27.609
Now what's interesting about
winning a bodybuilding show

00:17:27.609 --> 00:17:30.820
is that immediately
after you step off stage,

00:17:30.820 --> 00:17:34.510
people want to know what you
did to get into that shape.

00:17:34.510 --> 00:17:37.120
So the question that
had been avoiding

00:17:37.120 --> 00:17:41.530
my entire life, the question
of what do I eat, now

00:17:41.530 --> 00:17:44.630
became the most frequently
asked question to me.

00:17:44.630 --> 00:17:46.210
And I was put in
a position where

00:17:46.210 --> 00:17:48.730
I had to talk about
what I ate and how

00:17:48.730 --> 00:17:51.190
I was able to achieve these
results without following

00:17:51.190 --> 00:17:53.440
any type of traditional
bodybuilding diet that

00:17:53.440 --> 00:17:59.500
contained eggs, whey protein,
chicken, beef, or steak.

00:17:59.500 --> 00:18:01.840
And people became immediately
really intrigued in what

00:18:01.840 --> 00:18:05.140
I was saying, so I thought
to myself, why don't I

00:18:05.140 --> 00:18:06.562
share this journey online?

00:18:06.562 --> 00:18:08.020
And that's when I
made the decision

00:18:08.020 --> 00:18:09.940
to start trying
to educate people

00:18:09.940 --> 00:18:13.670
about an alternative approach to
reaching these kind of results,

00:18:13.670 --> 00:18:16.690
but not only that, an
alternative approach that also

00:18:16.690 --> 00:18:20.560
promoted health and longevity
from the inside out.

00:18:20.560 --> 00:18:24.010
And not long after,
I did another show,

00:18:24.010 --> 00:18:26.020
and I ended up winning
the entire thing again.

00:18:26.020 --> 00:18:29.260
And then shortly after that I
earned my professional status.

00:18:29.260 --> 00:18:32.170
And kind of my bodybuilding
career and my fitness career

00:18:32.170 --> 00:18:34.460
were paralleling
in the same way.

00:18:34.460 --> 00:18:36.700
But my passion for
bodybuilding was greatly

00:18:36.700 --> 00:18:39.430
exceeding my passion
for engineering.

00:18:39.430 --> 00:18:42.760
And more opportunities
began to present themselves

00:18:42.760 --> 00:18:44.970
like this one in the
form of public speaking.

00:18:44.970 --> 00:18:50.950
And I can remember I gave
this speech in London.

00:18:50.950 --> 00:18:55.210
And after giving this speech,
a gentleman came up to me,

00:18:55.210 --> 00:18:56.410
and he was in tears.

00:18:56.410 --> 00:18:59.590
And he embraced me, and he
goes, thank you so much.

00:18:59.590 --> 00:19:01.210
And I go, for what?

00:19:01.210 --> 00:19:03.820
And he goes, you
saved my mom's life.

00:19:03.820 --> 00:19:07.280
And I was really
blown away by that.

00:19:07.280 --> 00:19:08.500
And I go, how?

00:19:08.500 --> 00:19:11.560
And he goes, I found veganism
and the plant-based lifestyle

00:19:11.560 --> 00:19:12.490
through you.

00:19:12.490 --> 00:19:15.430
And you made me believe that
it was possible to be healthy.

00:19:15.430 --> 00:19:18.400
And through that process,
I helped my mom transition

00:19:18.400 --> 00:19:20.500
to a vegan diet, and she
was suffering from type

00:19:20.500 --> 00:19:25.870
2 diabetes so much so that she
was unable to get out of bed.

00:19:25.870 --> 00:19:29.450
And after adopting
a plant-based diet,

00:19:29.450 --> 00:19:31.910
she was able to almost
reverse and manage her type

00:19:31.910 --> 00:19:33.800
2 diabetes symptoms completely.

00:19:33.800 --> 00:19:38.470
And he fully believes that
that helped save her life.

00:19:38.470 --> 00:19:41.970
So whenever I came
back to work on Monday,

00:19:41.970 --> 00:19:43.500
I knew I had a decision to make.

00:19:43.500 --> 00:19:49.240
And I knew that I wasn't
spending my energy properly.

00:19:49.240 --> 00:19:51.460
And I knew that by
sharing this information

00:19:51.460 --> 00:19:53.380
it can not only help
people, but it can also

00:19:53.380 --> 00:19:56.350
help somebody save their life.

00:19:56.350 --> 00:19:58.360
So I walked into
my boss's office,

00:19:58.360 --> 00:20:02.950
and I put in my two weeks
resignation at that moment.

00:20:02.950 --> 00:20:06.550
And it was really quite
a very fulfilling moment

00:20:06.550 --> 00:20:08.920
in my life, but also
a very comical one

00:20:08.920 --> 00:20:11.200
because he asked
me, he said, Nimai,

00:20:11.200 --> 00:20:12.840
what are you going to do?

00:20:12.840 --> 00:20:15.340
And I tried to explain to him
what I was doing, and he goes,

00:20:15.340 --> 00:20:18.820
so you're quitting
engineering to become a vegan.

00:20:21.570 --> 00:20:26.380
And I'll never forget
it, but I believe

00:20:26.380 --> 00:20:28.840
that there is so much importance
in sharing this message

00:20:28.840 --> 00:20:32.530
and, particularly, to the
bodybuilding and fitness

00:20:32.530 --> 00:20:35.560
community because
bodybuilders in general

00:20:35.560 --> 00:20:39.640
consume two to three times more
protein than what they actually

00:20:39.640 --> 00:20:40.540
need.

00:20:40.540 --> 00:20:42.910
So this means that
bodybuilders are

00:20:42.910 --> 00:20:46.000
at a much higher risk of
developing these diseases later

00:20:46.000 --> 00:20:47.810
on in life.

00:20:47.810 --> 00:20:50.800
So just to give you an
idea of how much protein

00:20:50.800 --> 00:20:53.740
an average
bodybuilder consumes--

00:20:53.740 --> 00:20:56.230
normally, if you go to any
kind of bodybuilding website

00:20:56.230 --> 00:20:58.270
or read any kind of
fitness magazine,

00:20:58.270 --> 00:21:03.100
they recommend to eat at
least 1 to 2 grams of protein

00:21:03.100 --> 00:21:05.390
per pound of body weight.

00:21:05.390 --> 00:21:09.310
So let's give a hypothetical
example of this guy named Bob.

00:21:09.310 --> 00:21:14.180
So Bob the bodybuilder like
me weighs about 180 pounds.

00:21:14.180 --> 00:21:17.000
That would mean by following
that type of logic,

00:21:17.000 --> 00:21:21.190
you would have to get at least
180 to 360 grams of protein

00:21:21.190 --> 00:21:24.190
in order to build
and sustain muscle.

00:21:24.190 --> 00:21:27.190
So I started thinking,
what kind of impact

00:21:27.190 --> 00:21:31.800
does this have on the
world, and how many animals

00:21:31.800 --> 00:21:35.290
need to die in order to provide
Bob this amount of protein?

00:21:35.290 --> 00:21:38.250
So I reverse
calculated this figure,

00:21:38.250 --> 00:21:40.800
and let's just say
for simplicity's sake

00:21:40.800 --> 00:21:43.920
that Bob only consumed
chicken as his primary source

00:21:43.920 --> 00:21:44.490
of protein.

00:21:44.490 --> 00:21:47.990
So he wanted to get 180 grams
of protein from chicken.

00:21:47.990 --> 00:21:50.946
Now 1 ounce of chicken has
about 6 grams of protein.

00:21:50.946 --> 00:21:53.070
So that means he would need
at least on the low end

00:21:53.070 --> 00:21:55.860
to get at least 30 ounces
of chicken per day.

00:21:55.860 --> 00:21:58.230
Well, I looked up
how much usable meat

00:21:58.230 --> 00:21:59.724
is in a full grown chicken.

00:21:59.724 --> 00:22:01.140
And, normally,
full grown chickens

00:22:01.140 --> 00:22:02.610
weigh about 4 pounds
after you remove

00:22:02.610 --> 00:22:04.776
the feathers and everything
else that you don't eat.

00:22:04.776 --> 00:22:07.260
You're left with about
2 pounds of meat.

00:22:07.260 --> 00:22:11.520
So that means that Bob here
requires one chicken per day

00:22:11.520 --> 00:22:13.980
in order to build his muscles.

00:22:13.980 --> 00:22:17.210
If you think about
that for a second,

00:22:17.210 --> 00:22:20.180
what does that many
chickens look like?

00:22:20.180 --> 00:22:23.930
If you would imagine 365
chickens in this room,

00:22:23.930 --> 00:22:24.879
how loud would it be?

00:22:24.879 --> 00:22:25.920
What would it sound like?

00:22:25.920 --> 00:22:26.961
What would it smell like?

00:22:26.961 --> 00:22:30.500
There's so much life
with 365 living beings,

00:22:30.500 --> 00:22:32.405
and that's on the low
end of the spectrum.

00:22:32.405 --> 00:22:34.280
Think about it-- if he
goes with the high end

00:22:34.280 --> 00:22:38.640
of the spectrum, that's
almost 1,000 animals per year.

00:22:38.640 --> 00:22:41.750
Not only that, when I looked
into the deeper information

00:22:41.750 --> 00:22:44.780
in regards to how much
energy and resources

00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:48.920
it takes to feed these
chickens to get to that state,

00:22:48.920 --> 00:22:52.880
it takes roughly six times
the amount of grains and plant

00:22:52.880 --> 00:22:57.939
protein in order to produce
1 gram of animal protein.

00:22:57.939 --> 00:22:59.730
You don't have to be
an engineer to realize

00:22:59.730 --> 00:23:03.440
that's really inefficient.

00:23:03.440 --> 00:23:08.450
Next, approximately 83%
of agricultural land

00:23:08.450 --> 00:23:10.430
is used for livestock.

00:23:10.430 --> 00:23:15.050
And of that 83%, it
only provides about 18%

00:23:15.050 --> 00:23:17.180
of the world's calories.

00:23:17.180 --> 00:23:20.600
Again, very inefficient.

00:23:20.600 --> 00:23:22.910
And just to give you an
idea of how much resources

00:23:22.910 --> 00:23:25.880
it takes to raise these animals
and raise the crops that

00:23:25.880 --> 00:23:27.680
feed these animals--

00:23:27.680 --> 00:23:30.350
one hamburger in order
for it to reach your plate

00:23:30.350 --> 00:23:34.810
has about 660 gallons of
embedded water to get there.

00:23:37.500 --> 00:23:41.400
Approximately 27% of the
world's Freshwater consumption

00:23:41.400 --> 00:23:44.145
is used to produce crops
to feed the animals.

00:23:46.710 --> 00:23:50.640
In fact, along with
these amazing statistics

00:23:50.640 --> 00:23:54.420
is that animal agriculture
is approximately

00:23:54.420 --> 00:24:00.060
responsible for 18% of
greenhouse gas emissions

00:24:00.060 --> 00:24:04.330
according to the United
Nations Food of Agriculture.

00:24:04.330 --> 00:24:08.980
That is approximately equivalent
to all of the greenhouse gas

00:24:08.980 --> 00:24:13.600
emissions combined, such
as all the automobiles, all

00:24:13.600 --> 00:24:18.120
the planes, all the trains,
and all the ships combined.

00:24:18.120 --> 00:24:20.310
Let that sink in.

00:24:20.310 --> 00:24:26.220
On the other hand, let's say
you have a vegan bodybuilder.

00:24:26.220 --> 00:24:30.230
He requires zero
animals per year.

00:24:30.230 --> 00:24:32.650
And he still achieves
the exact same results.

00:24:32.650 --> 00:24:36.130
Not only that, but he
cuts out the middleman

00:24:36.130 --> 00:24:39.550
and goes straight to the
source and increases efficiency

00:24:39.550 --> 00:24:42.170
by up to six times.

00:24:42.170 --> 00:24:46.220
On top of that, he helped
save over 400,000 gallons

00:24:46.220 --> 00:24:49.820
of water per year simply by
choosing to eliminate his meat

00:24:49.820 --> 00:24:51.650
and dairy consumption.

00:24:51.650 --> 00:24:55.640
And he reduces approximately
11,000 square feet

00:24:55.640 --> 00:24:58.290
of deforestation per year.

00:24:58.290 --> 00:25:01.190
Now if you can imagine
everybody in this room reducing

00:25:01.190 --> 00:25:05.030
their meat consumption, just
the amount of profound effects

00:25:05.030 --> 00:25:07.340
it would have on the
environmental impact

00:25:07.340 --> 00:25:09.280
around us--

00:25:09.280 --> 00:25:13.920
in fact, if everybody in
the United States, which

00:25:13.920 --> 00:25:17.070
happens to consume
approximately three times more

00:25:17.070 --> 00:25:19.250
than the global average
of meat consumption--

00:25:19.250 --> 00:25:21.840
if the United States shifted
away from meat consumption

00:25:21.840 --> 00:25:25.290
to a plant-based diet, it would
reduce agricultural emissions

00:25:25.290 --> 00:25:25.910
by 73%.

00:25:28.810 --> 00:25:32.960
Now this all sounds nice in
theory, and it sounds great.

00:25:32.960 --> 00:25:35.950
But the question that
mostly everyone in this room

00:25:35.950 --> 00:25:40.740
must be wondering is, OK,
if I cut all this meat out

00:25:40.740 --> 00:25:45.480
and all those dairy, what
the heck do I eat, right?

00:25:45.480 --> 00:25:47.850
This is one of the
biggest challenges

00:25:47.850 --> 00:25:50.070
that I have as a
vegan influencer

00:25:50.070 --> 00:25:52.770
is to convince
people that vegans

00:25:52.770 --> 00:25:54.780
don't just only eat lettuce.

00:25:54.780 --> 00:25:56.890
And I could tell you
this a million times,

00:25:56.890 --> 00:25:59.130
but I would rather
just show you.

00:25:59.130 --> 00:26:05.460
So foods that I typically like
to eat consist of sushi, tacos,

00:26:05.460 --> 00:26:11.640
stir fry, sandwiches,
sometimes all at the same time,

00:26:11.640 --> 00:26:14.680
also burritos.

00:26:14.680 --> 00:26:16.750
You've got pizza.

00:26:16.750 --> 00:26:20.200
I mean, the possibilities
are absolutely endless when

00:26:20.200 --> 00:26:23.870
it comes to plant-based foods
that are not only delicious,

00:26:23.870 --> 00:26:26.750
but also very
nutritionally rich as well.

00:26:26.750 --> 00:26:29.950
So even different
types of cuisine,

00:26:29.950 --> 00:26:32.170
like Thai food or
Mediterranean--

00:26:32.170 --> 00:26:34.870
everything you see here is
completely plant-based and free

00:26:34.870 --> 00:26:37.200
of any kind of dairy
or animal products.

00:26:37.200 --> 00:26:39.160
As you can see, it
looks quite delicious,

00:26:39.160 --> 00:26:43.330
and I'll vouch for you
that it definitely was.

00:26:43.330 --> 00:26:45.190
So you might been
looking at those meals

00:26:45.190 --> 00:26:47.650
and been wondering
since you cut out

00:26:47.650 --> 00:26:51.520
all of the dairy and
the animal proteins,

00:26:51.520 --> 00:26:53.860
how much protein
are in these meals

00:26:53.860 --> 00:26:57.190
and is it enough to fully
sustain a healthy lifestyle,

00:26:57.190 --> 00:26:59.690
let alone build muscle?

00:26:59.690 --> 00:27:01.720
And this is another
question that I

00:27:01.720 --> 00:27:05.320
get asked every single day
at least 100 times a day.

00:27:05.320 --> 00:27:08.230
And if I had $1 for
every time that somebody

00:27:08.230 --> 00:27:10.360
asked me this question,
I would own my own island

00:27:10.360 --> 00:27:14.056
in the Caribbean
with an avocado farm.

00:27:14.056 --> 00:27:15.430
What's ironic
about this question

00:27:15.430 --> 00:27:17.980
is that most people who ask
this question don't even

00:27:17.980 --> 00:27:19.960
know how much they need.

00:27:19.960 --> 00:27:23.770
So the USDA actually
recommends 46 to 56 grams

00:27:23.770 --> 00:27:27.010
of protein per day for your
average sedentary person.

00:27:27.010 --> 00:27:30.640
To give you some perspective,
three cups of cooked lentils

00:27:30.640 --> 00:27:32.266
gives you 54 grams of protein.

00:27:32.266 --> 00:27:34.390
That's approximately 100%
of your daily recommended

00:27:34.390 --> 00:27:36.581
intake for protein.

00:27:36.581 --> 00:27:38.080
On top of that,
another study showed

00:27:38.080 --> 00:27:42.280
that vegans, in particular,
consume 70% more protein

00:27:42.280 --> 00:27:43.810
than they actually need.

00:27:43.810 --> 00:27:45.700
So there is no
shortage of protein

00:27:45.700 --> 00:27:48.290
when it comes to a vegan diet.

00:27:48.290 --> 00:27:52.480
However, athletes are different,
especially bodybuilders.

00:27:52.480 --> 00:27:54.160
They require a high
amount of protein

00:27:54.160 --> 00:27:56.650
because you are putting
your body under an insane

00:27:56.650 --> 00:27:58.194
amount of metabolic stress.

00:27:58.194 --> 00:27:59.860
You are breaking your
body down, and you

00:27:59.860 --> 00:28:02.510
need to regenerate and repair.

00:28:02.510 --> 00:28:04.730
So this requires protein.

00:28:04.730 --> 00:28:07.420
One of the largest
meta analyst that

00:28:07.420 --> 00:28:12.850
studied how much is optimal
protein for trained individuals

00:28:12.850 --> 00:28:16.330
determined that 1.8
grams per kilogram

00:28:16.330 --> 00:28:20.830
or 0.82 grams per pound
is the upper limit

00:28:20.830 --> 00:28:23.980
for protein consumption for
building and sustaining muscle.

00:28:23.980 --> 00:28:28.060
That means that anything
above 1.8 grams per kilogram

00:28:28.060 --> 00:28:30.730
did not show any more
meaningful results as far

00:28:30.730 --> 00:28:34.840
as building muscle
or building strength.

00:28:34.840 --> 00:28:37.420
Just to give you an example of
what that looks like-- again,

00:28:37.420 --> 00:28:40.460
somebody like my size
that's 180 pounds--

00:28:40.460 --> 00:28:42.490
you would multiply 0.82
times your body weight,

00:28:42.490 --> 00:28:45.130
and you would get
148 grams per day.

00:28:45.130 --> 00:28:48.280
That would be your my
necessary requirements

00:28:48.280 --> 00:28:49.940
for building and
maintaining muscle.

