00:30:43.890 --> 00:30:46.320
which is made from soy.

00:30:46.320 --> 00:30:52.020
Now soy has quite a lot
of conflicting information

00:30:52.020 --> 00:30:53.790
about it, and there's
a lot of phobia

00:30:53.790 --> 00:30:55.930
around consuming soy as well.

00:30:55.930 --> 00:30:57.780
One of the biggest
misconceptions

00:30:57.780 --> 00:31:02.040
is that soy contains
estrogen. Now I just

00:31:02.040 --> 00:31:04.230
want to set the record clear.

00:31:04.230 --> 00:31:08.290
Soy contains zero
estrogen. What soy contains

00:31:08.290 --> 00:31:10.380
is something called
phytoestrogens.

00:31:10.380 --> 00:31:12.780
Now these
phytoestrogens may have

00:31:12.780 --> 00:31:16.950
a similar molecular structure
to estrogen. So what happens

00:31:16.950 --> 00:31:20.400
is they can actually bind to
your estrogen receptor sites

00:31:20.400 --> 00:31:24.810
in your body and inhibit
real estrogen from attaching

00:31:24.810 --> 00:31:26.730
to those receptor sites.

00:31:26.730 --> 00:31:33.330
And in turn, what happens
is you lower your estrogen

00:31:33.330 --> 00:31:35.670
concentration in your body.

00:31:35.670 --> 00:31:39.510
And the way this happens is
that, as we mentioned earlier

00:31:39.510 --> 00:31:42.740
about drinking milk and
increasing estrogen levels,

00:31:42.740 --> 00:31:45.870
it actually decreases the risk
of certain types of cancers

00:31:45.870 --> 00:31:49.450
like prostate and breast cancer.

00:31:49.450 --> 00:31:53.290
Other studies show that it
does not affect testosterone

00:31:53.290 --> 00:31:55.250
or fertility at all.

00:31:55.250 --> 00:31:58.360
There has not been a single
study produced and published

00:31:58.360 --> 00:32:04.360
that conclude that it affects
testosterone in a negative way.

00:32:04.360 --> 00:32:07.570
Another big misconception
is that all soy is GMO.

00:32:07.570 --> 00:32:13.750
Now there is a wide variety
of USDA organic soy products

00:32:13.750 --> 00:32:16.930
that are available at
every single supermarket,

00:32:16.930 --> 00:32:18.580
and it's also
important to consider

00:32:18.580 --> 00:32:23.740
that a large percent of
the soy crops that are GMO

00:32:23.740 --> 00:32:28.240
are actually fed in animal feed.

00:32:28.240 --> 00:32:32.410
So these animals are consuming
high amounts of GMO soy,

00:32:32.410 --> 00:32:35.470
and then, again, you get it
secondhand through the animal

00:32:35.470 --> 00:32:37.810
whenever you consume that.

00:32:37.810 --> 00:32:39.570
So if you're trying
to avoid soy,

00:32:39.570 --> 00:32:43.290
you're still getting
it secondhand.

00:32:43.290 --> 00:32:45.780
So the next biggest
question is can a vegan diet

00:32:45.780 --> 00:32:47.760
provide me with all
the essential nutrients

00:32:47.760 --> 00:32:50.160
and vitamins that I need to
be healthy and to thrive?

00:32:50.160 --> 00:32:56.130
One of the most commonly talked
about vitamins that a vegan

00:32:56.130 --> 00:32:58.680
diet supposedly lacks is B12.

00:32:58.680 --> 00:33:02.130
Now it's important to
understand what is B12.

00:33:02.130 --> 00:33:08.720
Vitamin B12 is a vitamin that's
essential for optimal health.

00:33:08.720 --> 00:33:12.960
And the way it's produced
is it's commonly found--

00:33:12.960 --> 00:33:16.430
it's produced in bacteria
and commonly found in soil

00:33:16.430 --> 00:33:19.640
and in natural water sources.

00:33:19.640 --> 00:33:22.040
Having low amounts of
vitamin B12 in your system

00:33:22.040 --> 00:33:25.820
can produce symptoms like
fatigue, digestive issues,

00:33:25.820 --> 00:33:27.540
nerve issues, and
even vision loss.

00:33:27.540 --> 00:33:30.290
So it's really an
important vitamin.

00:33:30.290 --> 00:33:33.840
But this isn't a vegan problem.

00:33:33.840 --> 00:33:36.680
It's actually a general
population problem

00:33:36.680 --> 00:33:40.190
because approximately 40%
of the general population

00:33:40.190 --> 00:33:41.570
is low in B12.

00:33:41.570 --> 00:33:45.570
And there's a reason for this
is that we as humans used

00:33:45.570 --> 00:33:49.140
to get B12 through eating
trace amounts of soil that

00:33:49.140 --> 00:33:51.007
was on dirty or
unwashed vegetables.

00:33:51.007 --> 00:33:53.340
And we would consume that,
and that would be enough B12,

00:33:53.340 --> 00:33:56.130
or we would drink from
natural water sources.

00:33:56.130 --> 00:34:01.860
But over time through sanitary
and agricultural farming

00:34:01.860 --> 00:34:05.910
techniques, the pesticides,
and everything that is used,

00:34:05.910 --> 00:34:07.680
they inhibit any
kind of bacteria

00:34:07.680 --> 00:34:12.940
from forming or producing
these B12 for the bacteria.

00:34:12.940 --> 00:34:16.889
So, in fact, some
factory farm animals

00:34:16.889 --> 00:34:18.840
never even graze on soil.

00:34:18.840 --> 00:34:20.790
They never even see
daylight, so they

00:34:20.790 --> 00:34:23.760
have to supplement
these animals with B12.

00:34:23.760 --> 00:34:25.889
And a big misconception
is that B12 is only

00:34:25.889 --> 00:34:26.819
found through animals.

00:34:26.819 --> 00:34:28.860
But the reality is that
these animals are getting

00:34:28.860 --> 00:34:30.750
supplemented would
be 12, and then you

00:34:30.750 --> 00:34:33.360
get it secondhand by
consuming the animal.

00:34:33.360 --> 00:34:36.659
So a much more efficient
way to get your B12

00:34:36.659 --> 00:34:39.270
is to simply
supplement it yourself.

00:34:39.270 --> 00:34:43.860
And although this may not
seem like a natural thing

00:34:43.860 --> 00:34:47.100
to supplement a pill, well,
it's important to realize

00:34:47.100 --> 00:34:51.090
that we don't live in such
natural conditions anymore.

00:34:51.090 --> 00:34:53.130
And we've kind of
created this problem,

00:34:53.130 --> 00:34:57.030
and it's important that we have
to address it because everybody

00:34:57.030 --> 00:35:01.650
should take a look are what
their B12 levels are and decide

00:35:01.650 --> 00:35:05.110
whether or not to supplement.

00:35:05.110 --> 00:35:08.700
Next thing to consider
is omega-3 fatty acids.

00:35:08.700 --> 00:35:13.440
Now, fatty acids are
optimal for brain health,

00:35:13.440 --> 00:35:15.060
for managing blood
triglycerides,

00:35:15.060 --> 00:35:18.810
and also reducing inflammation.

00:35:18.810 --> 00:35:21.300
The most well-known source
of omega-3 fatty acids

00:35:21.300 --> 00:35:22.200
come from fish.

00:35:22.200 --> 00:35:24.780
So you've heard fish
are healthy for you,

00:35:24.780 --> 00:35:26.940
take your fish oil supplements.

00:35:26.940 --> 00:35:31.860
And the problem with that is
that fish and factory farming

00:35:31.860 --> 00:35:35.970
conditions, even
for fish farms, they

00:35:35.970 --> 00:35:39.280
have high levels of heavy
metals because the world's ocean

00:35:39.280 --> 00:35:41.760
supply and water supply
is so heavily contaminated

00:35:41.760 --> 00:35:43.020
with these heavy metals.

00:35:43.020 --> 00:35:47.344
And what happens is these
fish eat other fish,

00:35:47.344 --> 00:35:49.135
and these heavy metals
kind of concentrate.

00:35:49.135 --> 00:35:52.710
And they become more
bio-accumulated and stored

00:35:52.710 --> 00:35:55.050
in the fat cells of fish.

00:35:55.050 --> 00:35:56.940
And they store other
things too like PCBs

00:35:56.940 --> 00:35:58.350
and other heavy metals.

00:35:58.350 --> 00:36:00.756
And what happens is these
heavy metals, such as mercury--

00:36:00.756 --> 00:36:02.880
they can attack your system
in many different ways,

00:36:02.880 --> 00:36:05.190
particularly your
thyroid, which can

00:36:05.190 --> 00:36:08.490
have a great effect
on how efficiently

00:36:08.490 --> 00:36:11.150
your metabolism operates.

00:36:11.150 --> 00:36:15.140
Now an alternative source
of omega-3 fatty acids

00:36:15.140 --> 00:36:19.040
come from a wide variety of
plants, such as algae, chia

00:36:19.040 --> 00:36:23.540
seeds, hemp seeds, flax seeds,
walnuts, avocados, and Brussels

00:36:23.540 --> 00:36:25.180
sprouts.

00:36:25.180 --> 00:36:28.540
The difference is that
the form of omega-3s

00:36:28.540 --> 00:36:32.046
found in these sources
are what you call ALA.

00:36:32.046 --> 00:36:33.670
So there's three
different active types

00:36:33.670 --> 00:36:35.770
of omega-3 fatty acids.

00:36:35.770 --> 00:36:40.600
And our body has to convert
ALA omega-3 fatty acids

00:36:40.600 --> 00:36:44.530
into a more active component,
such as DHA and EPA, which

00:36:44.530 --> 00:36:47.720
are both very critical
for optimal health.

00:36:47.720 --> 00:36:51.740
Now this conversion process
can be very inefficient

00:36:51.740 --> 00:36:55.280
if your ratio of omega-6,
which is a very highly

00:36:55.280 --> 00:36:59.290
inflammatory fatty
acid, is too great

00:36:59.290 --> 00:37:02.000
to your omega-3 concentration.

00:37:02.000 --> 00:37:03.710
So, basically, you
want to optimize

00:37:03.710 --> 00:37:08.150
your omega-6 to omega-3 ratio
so you can convert as much ALA

00:37:08.150 --> 00:37:10.430
to DHA and EPA.

00:37:10.430 --> 00:37:13.580
Now foods that
contain omega-6 are

00:37:13.580 --> 00:37:15.560
things that are highly
processed-- things that

00:37:15.560 --> 00:37:18.330
contain canola oil, palm oil.

00:37:18.330 --> 00:37:20.200
All of these things
have really high amounts

00:37:20.200 --> 00:37:24.290
of omega-6, which not only
affect your ability to convert

00:37:24.290 --> 00:37:28.490
ALA to DHA, but also produce
a highly inflammatory state

00:37:28.490 --> 00:37:32.620
in your body, which can
again reduce blood flow.

00:37:32.620 --> 00:37:35.310
The next thing to
consider is vitamin D. Now

00:37:35.310 --> 00:37:40.080
vitamin D is essential
for calcium absorption

00:37:40.080 --> 00:37:42.580
and immune system support.

00:37:42.580 --> 00:37:45.640
Now, sunlight is needed
for the body's ability

00:37:45.640 --> 00:37:48.400
to produce vitamin
D. The problem is

00:37:48.400 --> 00:37:50.500
that not everybody goes
out into the sunlight,

00:37:50.500 --> 00:37:52.870
or there may not be enough
sunlight available, depending

00:37:52.870 --> 00:37:54.760
on which part of the
world you live in,

00:37:54.760 --> 00:37:58.060
to get enough sunlight
to produce vitamin D.

00:37:58.060 --> 00:38:00.070
And, again, this is
not a vegan issue.

00:38:00.070 --> 00:38:02.290
This is a worldwide
issue, and studies

00:38:02.290 --> 00:38:05.080
show that a large
population of the world

00:38:05.080 --> 00:38:09.270
is low or deficient
in vitamin D.

00:38:09.270 --> 00:38:12.730
So, again, it is just
best to supplement.

00:38:12.730 --> 00:38:15.840
And what's ironic
is that there's

00:38:15.840 --> 00:38:18.340
so many concerns
about a vegan diet

00:38:18.340 --> 00:38:21.890
not being able to provide
all the essential vitamins,

00:38:21.890 --> 00:38:23.830
minerals, and macronutrients.

00:38:23.830 --> 00:38:27.290
But according to the latest
US Dietary Guidelines,

00:38:27.290 --> 00:38:29.530
there are seven
critical nutrients

00:38:29.530 --> 00:38:33.890
that most Americans aren't
getting, such as calcium,

00:38:33.890 --> 00:38:39.550
potassium, fiber, magnesium,
vitamin A, C, and E.

00:38:39.550 --> 00:38:43.450
And what's interesting is that
these vitamins and minerals are

00:38:43.450 --> 00:38:48.310
found in abundance in
a plant-based diet.

00:38:48.310 --> 00:38:52.700
Now you might be thinking to
yourself, OK, I'm convinced.

00:38:52.700 --> 00:38:54.100
I want to give this thing a try.

00:38:54.100 --> 00:38:55.850
How do I start?

00:38:55.850 --> 00:38:57.970
So these are a few
tips that I suggest

00:38:57.970 --> 00:39:00.130
to how to successfully
transition

00:39:00.130 --> 00:39:01.660
into a plant based lifestyle.

00:39:01.660 --> 00:39:05.590
Now, I've had many conversations
and many interactions

00:39:05.590 --> 00:39:08.830
with people about how to make
the most efficient transition

00:39:08.830 --> 00:39:12.190
into a plant-based diet
that is sustainable,

00:39:12.190 --> 00:39:16.100
meaning it lasts you a lifetime.

00:39:16.100 --> 00:39:17.250
It's not a diet.

00:39:17.250 --> 00:39:18.500
It's a lifestyle change.

00:39:18.500 --> 00:39:20.780
Because what happens
is when most people try

00:39:20.780 --> 00:39:23.300
to go vegan and give up
all these other products,

00:39:23.300 --> 00:39:24.770
they become
overwhelmed, and they

00:39:24.770 --> 00:39:27.230
go back to what they
were originally doing.

00:39:27.230 --> 00:39:29.540
So what I suggest is
to slowly phase out

00:39:29.540 --> 00:39:32.620
animal products
at your own pace.

00:39:32.620 --> 00:39:36.390
You can swap out dairy products
for plant-based alternatives.

00:39:36.390 --> 00:39:39.520
There are a million different
plant-based alternatives,

00:39:39.520 --> 00:39:41.430
such as milk, butter, cheeses.

00:39:41.430 --> 00:39:43.440
You name it, they have it.

00:39:43.440 --> 00:39:45.390
The next thing
would be to swap out

00:39:45.390 --> 00:39:48.510
one for one, like for
like meat products

00:39:48.510 --> 00:39:50.130
with plant-based alternatives.

00:39:50.130 --> 00:39:51.660
You can still eat
the exact same way

00:39:51.660 --> 00:39:54.480
that you eat now,
just replace real meat

00:39:54.480 --> 00:39:57.530
with a plant-based
version of it.

00:39:57.530 --> 00:39:59.120
The next thing
would be to just try

00:39:59.120 --> 00:40:03.050
to replace one meal with
a vegan meal per day.

00:40:03.050 --> 00:40:05.630
And as you become more
accustomed to the variety

00:40:05.630 --> 00:40:07.490
of different foods
that you can eat,

00:40:07.490 --> 00:40:11.210
maybe try one
vegan day per week,

00:40:11.210 --> 00:40:13.310
and then eventually one
vegan week per month,

00:40:13.310 --> 00:40:16.070
and then one vegan
month per year,

00:40:16.070 --> 00:40:18.380
and then eventually
a fully transition

00:40:18.380 --> 00:40:21.210
plant-based lifestyle.

00:40:21.210 --> 00:40:24.750
There are also tons of resources
out there available to you

00:40:24.750 --> 00:40:28.020
if you have any concern about
anything regarding a vegan

00:40:28.020 --> 00:40:30.240
lifestyle or nutrition--

00:40:30.240 --> 00:40:32.130
things such as
veganfitness.com, which

00:40:32.130 --> 00:40:37.290
is a website that I started
along with my business partners

00:40:37.290 --> 00:40:39.270
just so we can help
educate athletes

00:40:39.270 --> 00:40:42.270
in particular about their
concerns and showing them

00:40:42.270 --> 00:40:45.240
that it's possible to
reach their athletic goals

00:40:45.240 --> 00:40:47.890
and not sacrifice any
performance at all.

00:40:47.890 --> 00:40:51.210
There are also things
like nutritionfacts.org,

00:40:51.210 --> 00:40:54.510
which is run by somebody
named Dr. Michael Gregor, who

00:40:54.510 --> 00:40:56.681
takes a look at almost
every single medical journal

00:40:56.681 --> 00:40:58.680
and every single medical
study that is published

00:40:58.680 --> 00:41:00.036
in regards to nutrition.

00:41:00.036 --> 00:41:01.410
There's also
another organization

00:41:01.410 --> 00:41:05.820
called Switch4Good, which is
an athlete-founded coalition

00:41:05.820 --> 00:41:10.680
of people who are educating
people about the dairy industry

00:41:10.680 --> 00:41:12.750
and some of the benefits
of giving that up.

00:41:12.750 --> 00:41:15.166
And there's also something
called the Physicians Committee

00:41:15.166 --> 00:41:17.040
for Responsible
Medicine, which is

00:41:17.040 --> 00:41:18.660
a coalition of
medical professionals

00:41:18.660 --> 00:41:21.390
that are trying
to bring awareness

00:41:21.390 --> 00:41:24.130
to the benefits of a
plant-based lifestyle.

00:41:24.130 --> 00:41:28.450
Now, before I end
this presentation,

00:41:28.450 --> 00:41:32.090
